%20is%20a%20wannabe%20filmmaker.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Finternational-film-festival-of-kerala-iffk-%5C%22%3EInternational%20Film%20Festival%20of%20Kerala%3C%2Fa%3E%20promoted%20by%20the%20state%20government%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%20been%20a%20big%20draw%20for%20Kerala's%20film%20buffs%20since%20it%20was%20founded%20in%201996.%20Before%20OTT%20platforms%20dominated%20the%20film%20landscape%2C%20cinephiles%20used%20to%20make%20a%20beeline%20for%20such%20festivals%20to%20watch%20foreign-language%20movies.%20In%20fact%2C%20well%20before%20that%2C%20there%20were%20film%20societies%20and%20art%20clubs%20bringing%20avant-garde%20films%20to%20even%20small%20towns%20in%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMalayalam%20cinema%20seems%20to%20be%20finally%20realising%20its%20potential%20in%20the%20age%20of%20streaming%2C%20but%20the%20'new%20wave'%20makers%20of%20today%20owe%20their%20filmmaking%20chops%20to%20the%20older%20generation%2C%20especially%20the%20class%20of%20the%20'70s.%20The%20likes%20of%20G.%20Aravindan%2C%20Adoor%20Gopalakrishnan%2C%20John%20Abraham%20are%20a%20few%20gems%20from%20that%20era.%20This%20was%20an%20age%20when%20films%20from%20the%20state%20regularly%20vied%20for%20top%20honours%20with%20Bengali%20cinema%20for%20national%20awards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Harikumar%20Was%20One%20Of%20His%20Kind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there%20were%20maestros%20such%20as%20P.N.%20Menon%2C%20K.G.%20George%20and%20Padmarajan%2C%20who%20made%20middle-of-the-road%20films%20that%20won%20critical%20and%20mass%20acclaim%20in%20equal%20measure.%20Ace%20director%20Harikumar%2C%20who%20passed%20away%20at%20the%20age%20of%2068%20last%20week%2C%20straddled%20that%20middle%20path.%20But%20there%20is%20something%20more%20unique%20to%20him%3A%20he%20traversed%20the%20distance%20between%20a%20connoisseur%20and%20a%20filmmaker%20seamlessly.%20Harikumar's%20passion%20for%20films%20was%20so%20compelling%20that%20it%20wasn't%20long%20before%20he%20became%20a%20filmmaker%20himself.%20There's%20a%20story%20to%20it%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20chance%20meeting%20with%20ace%20director%20George%20that%20changed%20the%20destiny%20of%20Harikumar%2C%20then%20a%20government%20servant%20with%20the%20town%20planning%20department%20in%20Kollam.%20George%20was%20struck%20by%20the%20sheer%20attention%20to%20detail%20in%20a%20cinema%20review%20written%20by%20Harikumar%20of%20his%20film%20%3Cem%3ESwapnadanam%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1976).%20And%20so%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20meet%20Harikumar%20in%20person%2C%20a%20meeting%20that%20ended%20up%20inspiring%20the%20latter%20to%20try%20his%20hand%20at%20filmmaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-malayalam-sleeper-hit-spotlights-unsung-heroes-of-2018-floods-4065196%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0Opinion%20-%20A%20Malayalam%20Sleeper%20Hit%20Spotlights%20Unsung%20Heroes%20Of%202018%20Floods%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20unlike%20George%2C%20a%20graduate%20from%20Pune's%20Film%20and%20Television%20Institute%20of%20India%2C%20Harikumar%20neither%20had%20formal%20training%20in%20filmmaking%20nor%20had%20he%20ever%20assisted%20a%20director.%20In%20the%20simplest%20of%20terms%2C%20he%20was%20a%20novice%2C%20but%20his%20keen%20observation%20and%20passion%20for%20cinema%20meant%20that%20Harikumar%20would%20eventually%20take%20to%20filmmaking%20like%20a%20duck%20to%20water.%20What%20set%20him%20apart%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20was%20an%20avid%20reader%2C%20which%20helped%20him%20choose%20unique%20subjects%20and%20treat%20them%20interestingly.%20His%20debut%20film%20%3Cem%3EAambalpoovu%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1981)%20was%20written%20by%20the%20Sahitya%20Akademi%20Award%20winner%20Perumbadavam%20Sreedharan%2C%20who%20many%20years%20later%20recalled%20that%20Harikumar%20never%20struck%20him%20as%20a%20newcomer%20while%20doing%20%3Cem%3EAambalpoovu%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Golden%20'90s%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarikumar%20soon%20went%20on%20to%20work%20with%20many%20prominent%20writers%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideos%2Foscars-2024-malayalam-film-2018-is-india-s-official-entry-727623%5C%22%3EKerala%20film%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20wrote%20both%20screenplays%20and%20dialogues%20for%20some%20of%20his%20early%20films%2C%20notably%20%3Cem%3EAyanam%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1985)%2C%20where%20he%20collaborated%20with%20John%20Paul.%20Two%20other%20films%2C%20%3Cem%3EJalakam%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1987)%20and%20%3Cem%3EOozham%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1988)%2C%20were%20collaborations%20with%20noted%20poet%20Balachandran%20Chullikkad.%20But%20it%20was%20the%20'90s%20that%20brought%20the%20best%20out%20of%20the%20director%20in%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarikumar%20did%20just%20three%20films%20-%20%3Cem%3EEzhunnallathu%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1991)%2C%20%3Cem%3ESukrutham%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1994)%20and%20%3Cem%3EUdyanapalakan%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1996)%20-%20that%20decade%20but%20they%20all%20stood%20out%20for%20their%20stories.%20If%20%3Cem%3EEzhunnallathu%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20about%20a%20young%20man's%20search%20for%20his%20older%20brother%2C%20an%20illegitimate%20child%2C%20%3Cem%3EUdyanapalakan%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20about%20a%20grumpy%20ex-serviceman%20tending%20to%20his%20garden%20in%20a%20typical%20village%20setting%20and%20the%20relationship%20he%20develops%20with%20a%20young%20girl%20moving%20in%20next%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOf%20Love%2C%20Loss%20And%20Life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20%3Cem%3ESukrutham%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethough%20that%20remains%20Harikumar's%20most%20memorable%20film.%20Of%20course%2C%20this%20was%20also%20on%20account%20of%20its%20terrific%20screenplay%20by%20the%20accomplished%20M.T.%20Vasudevan%20Nair%2C%20whose%20vision%20could%20be%20translated%20fully%20on-screen%20by%20the%20director.%20Sukrutham's%20opening%20shot%20takes%20us%20to%20a%20hospital%20where%20the%20protagonist%2C%20Ravishankar%2C%20essayed%20by%20Mammootty%2C%20is%20undergoing%20treatment%20for%20terminal%20blood%20cancer.%3Cbr%3E%5CnRavishankar's%20young%20wife%2C%20Malini%20(played%20by%20Gowthami)%2C%20and%20their%20common%20friend%2C%20Rajendran%20(Manoj%20K.%20Jayan)%2C%20are%20by%20his%20side%2C%20but%20when%20Ravishankar%20realises%20his%20days%20are%20numbered%2C%20he%20expresses%20his%20wish%20to%20move%20back%20to%20his%20ancestral%20village%20and%20spend%20his%20last%20days%20there.%20There%2C%20he%20is%20cared%20for%20by%20his%20childhood%20sweetheart%2C%20Durga%20(Shanthi%20Krishna).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fmumbai-film-festival-2023-seven-must-watch-south-asian-films-that-tackle-urgent-themes-4515535%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0Mumbai%20Film%20Festival%202023%3A%20Seven%20Must-Watch%20South%20Asian%20Films%20That%20Tackle%20Urgent%20Themes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavishankar's%20impending%20death%20takes%20a%20toll%20on%20everyone%20around%20him%2C%20including%20the%20protagonist%2C%20who%2C%20in%20a%20moment%20of%20weakness%2C%20persuades%20Malini%20to%20move%20on%20and%20get%20hitched%20to%20Rajendran%20after%20his%20passing.%20The%20more%20time%20Ravishankar%20spends%20in%20his%20ancestral%20home%2C%20the%20more%20the%20grief%20of%20what%20could've%20been%20engulfs%20him.%20Then%20comes%20a%20twist%3A%20an%20old%20doctor-friend%20of%20his%20coaxes%20him%20to%20undergo%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20therapy%20at%20the%20latter's%20wellness%20centre.%20There's%20only%20one%20condition%3A%20a%20strong%20urge%20to%20live%20is%20imperative%20for%20this%20treatment%20to%20succeed.%20Perhaps%20partly%20influenced%20by%20the%20days%20he%20spent%20in%20his%20village%2C%20Ravishankar%20is%20cured%20miraculously%20within%20a%20few%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20sombre%20jolt%20awaits%20him%20when%20he%20tries%20to%20start%20life%20afresh.%20In%20his%20ancestral%20home%2C%20he%20is%20rebuffed%20by%20Durga%2C%20who%20says%20she%20was%20merely%20taking%20pity%20on%20him.%20Malini%20has%20gone%20ahead%20and%20has%20planned%20a%20life%20with%20Rajendran%3B%20both%20resent%20his%20return.%20Back%20at%20his%20newspaper%20office%2C%20Ravishankar%20is%20told%20that%20his%20deputy%20has%20taken%20over%20his%20cubicle.%20What's%20more%2C%20he%20finds%20an%20obituary%20tucked%20neatly%20inside%20a%20drawer.%20Ravishankar%20edits%20it%20himself%2C%20and%20the%20piece%20makes%20it%20to%20print%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20final%20scenes%2C%20as%20the%20end%20credits%20roll%2C%20Ravishankar%20is%20seen%20walking%20toward%20a%20dark%20railway%20tunnel%20with%20the%20sound%20of%20a%20speeding%20train%20approaching%20him%20in%20the%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Film%20That%20Leaves%20You%20With%20Existential%20Questions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESukrutham%3C%2Fem%3E%20stays%20with%20you%20long%20after%20you%20watch%20it%2C%20leaving%20you%20with%20complex%20existential%20questions.%20M.T.%20Vasudevan%20Nair%20has%20dealt%20with%20similar%20themes%20of%20death%20and%20mortality%20in%20films%20like%20%3Cem%3EAalkkoottathil%20Thaniye%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1984)%2C%20albeit%20in%20different%20settings.%20The%20climax%20sequence%20of%20%3Cem%3EBandhanam%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1978)%2C%20written%20and%20directed%20by%20him%2C%20ended%20with%20the%20pronouncement%3A%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20sin%20of%20your%20birth%2C%20you%20are%20condemned%20to%20live%20till%20you%20die%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20surprisingly%2C%20and%20perhaps%20symbolically%2C%20Harikumar%20named%20his%20Thiruvananthapuram%20home%20after%20%3Cem%3ESukrutham%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20film%20he%20came%20to%20be%20best%20known%20for.%20He%20reasoned%20that%20the%20movie%20marked%20his%20identity%20as%20a%20filmmaker%20for%20all%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESwayamvara%20Panthal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2000)%2C%20another%20memorable%20film%20by%20him%2C%20may%20have%20had%20some%20shades%20of%20Balu%20Mahendra's%201982%20Tamil%20film%20%3Cem%3EMoondram%20Pirai%3C%2Fem%3E%20(remade%20in%20Hindi%20as%20%3Cem%3ESadma%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20have%20the%20same%20tragic%20ending.%20That%2C%20ironically%2C%20might%20have%20robbed%20its%20lead%2C%20Jayaram%2C%20of%20the%20state%20award%20he%20won%20for%20the%20Best%20Second%20Actor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarikumar%20did%20not%20manage%20to%20make%20such%20films%20post%20that%20phase%2C%20though%20he%20remained%20very%20much%20active%20in%20Mollywood%20as%20a%20director%20and%20national%20film%20award%20jury%20member.%20Only%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20back%2C%20he%20had%20made%20a%20comeback%20with%20%3Cem%3EAutorickshakkarante%20Bharya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20adapted%20from%20writer%20M.%20Mukundan's%20story%2C%20once%20again%20underlining%20how%20much%20Malayalam%20literature%20influenced%20his%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMalayalam%20cinema%20is%20seeing%20a%20blockbuster%20year%20with%20films%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Flal-salaam-director-aishwarya-on-films-failure-and-the-rajinikanth-factor-5194099%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EManjummel%20Boys%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EAadujeevitham%20Aavesham%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EPremalu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EBhramayugam%20%3C%2Fem%3Eet%20al%20winning%20plaudits%20today%20not%20just%20in%20Kerala%20but%20even%20nationally.%20A%20lot%20of%20history%20has%20gone%20into%20this%20journey%2C%20shaped%20and%20nurtured%20by%20filmmakers%20like%20Harikumar%2C%20the%20man%20who%20followed%20his%20dream%20and%20remained%20true%20to%20it%20till%20the%20very%20end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Anand%20Kochukudy%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20and%20columnist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715934120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22htt