pt-124051700337_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fopenai-enters-into-google-ecosystem-with-drive-integration-in-chatgpt-124051700337_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Scientists%20Recreate%20Face%20Of%20Egyptian%20King%20And%20%26quot%3BRichest%20Man%20Who%20Ever%20Lived%26quot%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20created%20the%20face%20of%20an%20Egyptian%20king%2C%20who%20is%20considered%20the%20richest%20man%20who%20ever%20lived.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%2C%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20in%203%2C400%20years%20that%20the%20face%20of%20Amenhotep%20III%2C%20the%20grandfather%20of%20Tutenkhamun%2C%20has%20been%20recreated.%20Amenhotep%20III%20ruled%20Egypt%20in%20the%2014th%20century%20BC%2C%20at%20the%20height%20of%20its%20power%2C%20and%20was%20worshipped%20as%20living%20god.%20He%20led%20the%20country%20through%20a%20period%20of%20unprecedented%20prosperity%20and%20international%20power.%20Amenhotep%20III%20is%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20pharaohs%20and%20has%20more%20surviving%20statues%20than%20any%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20multinational%20team%20used%20the%20data%20from%20skull%20of%20his%20mummy%20to%20reveal%20how%20Amenhotep%20III%20really%20looked%20like.%20They%20then%20used%20data%20from%20living%20donors%20to%20approximate%20the%20dimensions%20and%20position%20of%20his%20nose%2C%20ears%2C%20eyes%20and%20lips.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20are%20not%20mistaken%2C%20this%20is%20the%20first%20facial%20approximation%20of%20Amenhotep%20III.%20It%20is%20our%20gift%20to%20all%20those%20who%20appreciate%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2024%2F05%2F16%2Flifestyle%2Fface-of-richest-man-in-history-tutankhamuns-grandfather-amenhotep-iii-revealed%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EPost%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20quoted%20Brazilian%20graphics%20designer%20Cicero%20Moraes%2C%20who%20resurrected%20the%20famous%20Pharaoh's%20face%2C%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20amazed%20with%20the%20final%20result%3B%20seeing%20a%20complete%20bust%20with%20these%20colours%20and%20the%20facial%20serenity%20is%20quite%20satisfying.%20Compared%20to%20other%20approximations%20of%20pharaohs%20that%20I%20have%20participated%20in%2C%20this%20was%20the%20most%20complete%20too%2C%20as%20we%20modelled%20the%20clothes%20and%20accessories%2C%26quot%3B%20Moraes%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmenhotep%20was%20named%20after%20the%20sun%20and%20air%20god%20Amun%2C%20who%20he%20claimed%20was%20his%20real%20father.%20He%20undertook%20massive%20building%20contracts%20in%20Egypt%20and%20Nubia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EPost%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said%20that%20the%20wealth%20of%20the%20Egyptian%20king%20was%20unparalleled%2C%20citing%20his%20diplomatic%20letters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20speculations%20that%20the%20mummy%20of%20Amenhotep%20III%20may%20have%20been%20entirely%20covered%20with%20gold%20leaf%2C%20so%20that%20he%20must%20have%20looked%20like%20a%20statue%20of%20a%20god%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Michael%20Habicht%2C%20an%20archaeologist%20at%20Flinders%20University%20in%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20expert%20said%20Amenhotep%20III%20was%20an%20obese%2C%20sick%2C%20and%20sedentary%20man%2C%20who%20was%20almost%20bald%2C%20and%20suffered%20from%20dental%20problems.%20His%20body%20height%20is%20about%20156cm%20(around%205ft1)%2C%20making%20him%20one%20of%20the%20smallest%20kings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20might%20well%20have%20been%20one%20of%20the%20richest%20men%20that%20ever%20lived%2C%20at%20least%20in%20his%20epoch%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Habicht.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20died%20at%20the%20age%20of%2040%20or%2050%20in%201352%20BC%2C%20said%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715926980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fgl25vlm8_amenhotep-iii-fa