%20for%20everyone.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660c036c3f923f7dab037214%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223355%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20has%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20advancing%20AI%20is%20a%20top%20priority%20for%20the%20company.%3Cp%3EJOSH%20EDELSON%2FGETTY%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20layoffs%20aren't%20necessarily%20a%20signal%20that%20the%20company%20isn't%20doing%20well.%20The%20company's%20market%20cap%20has%20nearly%20quadrupled%20since%202015%2C%20reaching%20%241.7%20trillion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20other%20tech%20companies%2C%20the%20layoffs%20are%20rooted%20in%20two%20main%20areas%3A%20over-hiring%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20restructuring%20for%20the%20AI%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%202023%20layoff%20announcement%2C%20Pichai%20said%20the%20company%20experienced%20%26quot%3Bdramatic%20growth%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20To%20match%20that%20growth%2C%20Google%20hired%20%26quot%3Bfor%20a%20different%20economic%20reality%20than%20the%20one%20we%20face%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20number%20of%20our%20teams%20made%20changes%20to%20become%20more%20efficient%20and%20work%20better%2C%20remove%20layers%2C%20and%20align%20their%20resources%20to%20their%20biggest%20product%20priorities%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Google%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20changes%20give%20employees%20a%20chance%20to%20work%20on%20Google's%20most%20innovative%20advances%20while%20reducing%20bureaucracy%2C%20which%2045%25%20of%20employees%20said%20was%20slowing%20down%20their%20work%20in%20a%202023%20companywide%20survey%20reviewed%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20continues%20to%20hire%20talent%2C%20even%20amid%20the%20layoffs%2C%20and%20currently%20has%20a%20number%20of%20open%20listings%20on%20its%20site%2C%20most%20of%20which%20are%20in%20engineering%2